{
  "texts": [
    "Educational games face many additional challenges.",
    "On a socio-cultural dimension (Fernández-Manjón et al., 2015), an issue is social rejection of games, which may be reduced by improving society's understanding of games as another form of cultural good, and informing stakeholders (students, educators, and parents) about the social potential and positive effects of video games (Granic et al., 2014) and their usefulness in education (Bourgonjon et al., 2010).",
    "At the same time, violence, sexism, and discrimination are advised to be avoided in the design of educational games (Fernández-Manjón et al., 2015).",
    "Along an educational dimension, limited accessibility to educational games can prevent their further adoption in education (Fernández-Manjón et al., 2015).",
    "Whereas creating and maintaining user manuals and best practice guides are ways to facilitate accessibility (Fernández-Manjón et al., 2015), both require further structural support."
  ]
}